reviews.limitations:
- The fact that Circle-RoPE does not preserve the 2D geometry of the image in any strict sense; 

- The spurious positional bias is an indexing artifact, but a trained model may compensate for it through the attention weights. If, during full pre-training, the model learns to ignore this positional bias, then Circle-RoPE is basically solving a problem that may not even exist. 

- What’s really needed are experiments showing that this bias actually affects final performance under large-scale training
